019s silhouette, but she could feel her warmth. It was an ache that had \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u044c constant in Ginny\u2019s chest, a heavy, shimmering longing that Hermione seemed utterly immune to.\n\nWhen Hermione\u2019s breathing finally leveled out into the slow, deep rhythm of sleep, Ginny turned onto her side. She reached down, her fingers finding the hem of her nightdress, sliding beneath it to find the familiar, aching heat between her legs. \n\nShe kept her eyes on the dark shape of Hermione beside her. Each shallow breath, each toss and turn of the other girl, drove the intensity higher. Ginny let herself imagine Hermione's hands instead of her own, the touch she craved more than anything else in the world. The low ceiling of the attic seemed to close in around her, making her feel isolated and daring. Her movements grew more urgent as the fantasy blurred the line between her own hands and the woman sleeping inches away.\n\nIn the darkness, Hermione stirred. She groaned softly and shifted, her leg sliding haphazardly upward and then firmly over Ginny\u2019s thigh. \n\nThe dead weight\u2014the sudden, searing heat of hermione\u2019s leg against her own\u2014shattered Ginny\u2019s focus. The sensation pushed her over the edge. She sucked in her breath, her body jolting with the sudden, rhythmic piercings of a climax. She fought to contain the sound, her muscles locking and twisting as waves of pleasure crashed over her.\n\nHermione was wide awake instantly. \"Ginny?\" she whispered, her voice thick with sleep but sharp with alarm. She reached out, her hand finding Ginny\u2019s shoulder and shaking it. \"Ginny, what\u2019s wrong? Are you\u2014are you all right?\"\n\nGinny couldn't speak; she was lost in the violent, trembling force of her own body, her legs kicking beneath the covers in a desperate attempt to hold onto the sensation and at once push it away. \n\nHearing the frantic motion, Hermione bolted up. \"Oh my god\u2014are you having a seizure?\" Her voice was tight, panicked. \"Let me see\u2014where are you hurting?\" She began fumbling blindly in the dark, trying to find the lamp, her breath coming in quick, anxious bursts. \"Talk to me. Give me a sign if you can still hear me. Someone!\" she called out, glancing toward the door. \"Mum! Ron! Anyone up?\"\n\n\"No...\" Ginny croaked, the words spilling out of her, strained and wet. She felt the tremors begin to subside, leaving her limp and radiant. \"Please,\" she gasped, reaching out to catch Hermione\u2019s hand. \"You\u2019re... making it worse. Stop.\"\n\n\"I can't stop!\" Hermione was taut with worry, barely leaning over her. \"I don't know what's happening\u2014you were fine a second ago. Maybe you've been sick, maybe there's a toxin\u2014\"\n\n\"Hermione,\" Ginny interrupted, her voice a jagged whisper. She swallowed hard, looking up at the silhouette of the girl she loved\u2014who saw her as nothing more than a roommate. \"It\u2019s not a seizure. I was... I wanted you.\"\n\nHermione went still.\n\n\"I was touching myself,\" Ginny said, her voice trembling. \"And you moved, and it...\" She couldn't finish; she just closed her eyes, waiting.\n\nHermione said nothing.", "embedding": [0.037017229944467545, -0.010286507196724415, 0.038115277886390686, 0.1030086949467659, 0.0256610456854105, -0.011626043356955051, 0.02662619575858116, 0.029901552945375443, 0.06257583945989609, 0.03098757192492485, -0.059555355459451675, -0.032827433198690414, -0.010862831957638264, 0.04196648672223091, 0.024332808330655098, 0.01618189364671707, 0.025574941188097, -0.023643894121050835, -0.09930228441953659, 0.06367771327495575, 0.035280559211969376, 0.013852708972990513, 0.018910152837634087, -0.01571713574230671, 0.054033905267715454, -0.02423420548439026, -0.007135381456464529, -0.058436740189790726, -0.039810869842767715, 0.014873500913381577, -0.03935515135526657, -0.0030735379550606012, -0.10279832780361176, -0.010357331484556198, 0.03025948815047741, 0.0675135552883